The Role

We currently have an exciting opportunity for a results driven marketing professional to support the Marketing team with delivering marketing initiatives. This role will be primarily responsible for managing day to day activities for our key fitness/lifestyle brands.

This is a challenging and fast paced role located in NYC working within the busy Marketing team.

Tasks

Key Responsibilities

Reporting to the Marketing Manager, your responsibilities will include:


The coordination and implementation of marketing plan activities across the full marketing spectrum – product, price, promotion & place, across all touch points and channels.
Weekly review, update & maintenance of Websites. Uploading new campaigns and other required content.
Work with key marketing suppliers to deliver quality and cost effective print production outcomes across all marketing collateral including brochures, display fit outs, signage and POS;
Assist in the coordination and execution of the media plan. This includes liaising with various media outlets and media agencies on specifications, timings and requirements;
To ensure all marketing materials and advertising meet brand guidelines, have been thoroughly proof read and have been compliance checked and approved before finalising and sending to print or media;
Coordinate other projects and administration as required, e.g. Awards, Events, Promotional merchandise sourcing, Invoicing, HR or other internal stakeholder support, etc;
Brief and coordinate EDMs to the database – new promotions, new displays, latest news;

Requirements

The Essentials

To be successful in this position, you will also have the following skills, knowledge and attributes:


Tertiary Marketing qualification;
Minimum of 1 year experience in a similar marketing role in a fast paced, results driven environment, construction industry experience a positive;
Experience planning events and flexibility to work evenings and weekends to manage events where required;
Proven ability to manage competing priorities with a high attention to detail;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills and ability to liaise with stakeholders at all levels of the business;
A highly organised approach to managing projects with the ability to prioritise tasks effectively;
Experience in the fitness industry is preferred but not essential

Benefits

The Reward


Competitive Remuneration Package
Health Care and Insurance Plans
Wellness Programs
WeWork Access Around the Globe
Family Care

How to Apply

We move quickly at HYDE and continually review applications, so if you don't want to miss out, apply today below. Note that we prefer to deal with you directly; we haven't briefed a recruitment agency on this role and won't be accepting CVs through any recruitment agency, so please apply directly.

In light of COVID-19, we are frequently reviewing our recruitment processes. Right now, we are conducting all interviews virtually. This is a fluid situation and we will adapt our processes as we need to with any government guidelines or regulations.

